there.

21:01.060 --> 21:04.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The migration
debate is dominating
the political landscape, and the
latest polls

21:04.697 --> 21:09.835 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
show rises for the main
center-right opposition
party, and in the lead are the
anti-immigrant

21:09.935 --> 21:13.339 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Sweden Democrats. Their
integration spokesman
is Markus Wiechel.

21:13.439 --> 21:16.876 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARKUS WIECHEL, Sweden
Democrats: Well, society
is pretty much falling apart.
The government

21:16.976 --> 21:22.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is actually taking money from
the foreign
aid budgets to fund refugees
coming to Sweden.

21:22.114 --> 21:26.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I'm not sure I'm going to
call them refugees,
actually, because they have
crossed seven

21:26.919 --> 21:31.657 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or eight more safe countries on
their way
to Sweden. They're economic
