the risks
of what's really a quite
biologically extreme

32:17.536 --> 32:23.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
procedure, whether that's worth
what their
-- their preference to have a
genetically

32:23.308 --> 32:25.143 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
related child is.

32:25.243 --> 32:30.482 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
All people that have this
problem, this terrible
problem, can have healthy
children, children

32:30.582 --> 32:35.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who are not affected by these
mitochondrial
diseases, in the ways that Jeff
just mentioned,

32:35.854 --> 32:39.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and some of them can actually
use an embryo
screening technology as well.
And that would

32:39.724 --> 32:44.362 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
further reduce the number of
people who would
be candidates for this
procedure.

32:44.462 --> 32:49.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, for the rest of us, I
think we have
to weigh the preferences of
those -- that

32:49.901 --> 32:55.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
small number of people for a
genetically related
child against -- which is a
benefit, but it's

32:55.907 --> 33:01.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a social benefit, not really a
medical benefit,
because it's not about healthy
children.

33:01.413 --> 33:07.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have to weigh that against
the big deal
it is to do this for the first
time, to make

33:07.586 --> 33:13.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
changes that would be passed
down to future
generations. And this problem of
whether we

33:13.692 --> 33:19.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
should do it or not is a subject
right now
of huge controversy around a
different technique

33:19.264 --> 33:21.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
called gene editing.

33:21.700 --> 33:26.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on that technique, the
conclusion of a
500-person meeting that was held
in December

33:26.771 --> 33:32.377 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
was that it would be
irresponsible to proceed
unless and until there was a
broad, societal

33:32.477 --> 33:34.646 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
consensus that it would be OK.

33:34.746 --> 33:39.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, on the other hand, the
committee, although
I appreciate very much the
cautions and the

33:40.018 --> 33:44.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
limitations that they have
recommended, but
this committee is saying it's OK
to go forward

33:44.923 --> 33:46.758 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
now.

33:46.858 --> 33:48.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Jeffrey, what
do you make
of that? Is this the slippery
slope to gene

33:48.927 --> 33:51.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
editing or some of these more
troubling outcomes?

33:51.396 --> 33:55.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY KAHN: I would say no,
and here's why.

33:55.667 --> 34:00.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As Marcy rightly pointed out,
there are real
concerns about crossing the germ
line, so

34:00.205 --> 34:05.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
creating genetic modifications
that could
be inherited by future
generations. And among

34:05.143 --> 34:09.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the recommendations in our
report was that
the initial investigations be
limited to the

34:09.514 --> 34:14.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
implantation of male embryos,
because the
mitochondrial DNA is only passed
from mother

34:14.753 --> 34:16.521 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to offspring.

34:16.621 --> 34:21.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So by limiting the offspring to
males, you
wouldn't allow that germ line
modification

34:21.192 --> 34:26.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to happen. There would be no
possibility of
passing those alterations to
future generations.

34:26.498 --> 34:32.170 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we thought we could find a
way to allow
people who very much wanted to
have genetically

34:32.270 --> 34:36.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
related offspring to pursue a
new reproductive
technology.

34:36.207 --> 34:39.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think it's important to
say there are
many new reproductive
technologies introduced

34:40.045 --> 34:44.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in this country and around the
world that
do not get this level of
scrutiny. This is

34:44.115 --> 34:48.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the first time the Food and Drug
Administration
in our country has, from the
beginning, prior

34:48.386 --> 34:54.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the initial investigation of
a new reproductive
technology, has asked for this
level of scrutiny,

34:54.192 --> 34:58.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and, depending on what they do
with the recommendations
from this report, implement them
in a way

34:58.196 --> 35:02.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that will really control the
introduction
of a new technology of this
sort.

35:02.200 --> 35:05.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Marcy, what do
you make
of that? Do you feel that the
conditions can

35:06.037 --> 35:10.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be placed on this technology to
keep it in
check that would make you
comfortable with

35:10.375 --> 35:12.110 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
this?

35:12.210 --> 35:15.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCY DARNOVSKY: Well, the
condition that
I would like to see placed on
this before

35:15.981 --> 35:21.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we go forward would be for the
United States
to join the dozens of other
countries around

35:21.219 --> 35:25.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the world that have actually
written laws
saying that we're not going to
alter the nuclear

35:25.957 --> 35:29.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DNA that's passed down to our
children and
future generations.

35:29.861 --> 35:37.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that would make us able
to evaluate
this technology in a better way.
And the limitations

35:37.669 --> 35:43.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are better than nothing, but
they are temporary,
as the report notes, and I think
we're already

35:43.975 --> 35:51.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
seeing this approval being
characterized as
a green light for going ahead,
and it's being

35:51.683 --> 35:57.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
used as an argument for doing
the full-out
kinds of genetic engineering
that would create

35:57.922 --> 35:59.324 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the designer baby scenarios.

35:59.424 --> 36:01.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right,
this is a very
interesting discussion.

36:02.093 --> 36:06.798 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Marcy Darnovsky and Jeffrey
Kahn, thank you
both very much for being here.

36:06.898 --> 36:11.603 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY KAHN: Thank you.

36:11.703 --> 36:16.374 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARCY DARNOVSKY: Thank you.

36:16.474 --> 36:24.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now: using big
data to assess
medical treatments and
interventions and whether

36:24.482 --> 36:29.320 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
decisions for individual
patients are the
right choice for all of society.

36:29.421 --> 36:34.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's not necessarily seen as
the right way
of making decisions in science
and medicine

36:34.159 --> 36:38.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when lives are at stake. But
some believe
it's a critical consideration.

36:38.797 --> 36:44.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our science correspondent Miles
O'Brien looks
at how some thinkers in the
field are challenging

36:44.436 --> 36:46.171 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
long-held assumptions.

36:46.271 --> 36:52.877 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The story was produced in
collaboration with
the Pulitzer Center on Crisis
Reporting.

36:52.977 --> 37:02.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: This is where the
line between
life and death is drawn, an
operating room

37:02.153 --> 37:05.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at a hospital in a remote part
of Nepal.

37:05.523 --> 37:12.130 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Dr. Shree Ram Tiwari is
performing one of
the first C-sections in this
part of the world,

37:12.230 --> 37:21.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hoping to save the lives of Muna
Buhl (ph)
and her unborn child. It's not
going smoothly.

37:21.806 --> 37:28.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. SHREE RAM TIWARI, Physician
(through translator):
The power cut out at such an
important time,

37:28.880 --> 37:35.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because the baby should keep
crying after
it's born, but it wasn't. We
needed power

37:35.854 --> 37:38.089 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the suction machine.

37:38.189 --> 37:43.695 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: Bringing
C-sections to this
remote corner comes not only
with risks, but

37:43.795 --> 37:50.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
also a hefty price tag. The
bills are paid
by Possible, the American
charity that runs

37:50.101 --> 37:51.903 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the hospital.

37:52.003 --> 37:54.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. SHREE RAM TIWARI (through
translator):
Nepal's constitution talks about
health rights,

37:54.873 --> 38:00.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that every person should have
access to health
care. But that is not
implemented.

38:00.512 --> 38:06.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: While mother and
child remain
the focus for Dr. Tiwari as he
copes with

38:07.051 --> 38:13.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the power failure, the global
health community
tries to shed light on whether
this surgery

38:13.658 --> 38:17.795 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
should have happened at all.

38:17.896 --> 38:23.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Medical ethicist Peter Singer is
a professor
at Princeton University. He is a
leading proponent

38:23.835 --> 38:26.137 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of a philosophy called effective
altruism.

38:26.237 --> 38:29.741 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PETER SINGER, Princeton
University: Effective
altruists look for those health
care programs

38:29.841 --> 38:35.380 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
worldwide that offer the
low-hanging fruit.
Where can you save lives most
cheaply?

38:35.480 --> 38:40.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: Effective
altruists like Dr.
Singer compare different
interventions, and

38:40.285 --> 38:44.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
choose the one that provides the
most bang
for the buck. They might elect
to pay for

38:45.089 --> 38:48.660 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
community health workers, rather
than operating
rooms.

38:48.760 --> 38:54.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But human beings are not wired
to respond
in this dispassionate,
systematic manner.

38:55.099 --> 38:58.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is why commercial appeals
for charities
often look like this:

38:58.736 --> 39:06.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: Tiny, vulnerable Aisha
won't eat
tonight or tomorrow. She is
slowly dying.

39:06.511 --> 39:12.116 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PETER SINGER: We are
psychologically adapted
to respond to individuals who we
can see.

39:12.217 --> 39:17.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But health care is a scarce
resource. So,
data is absolutely critical. We
can't know

39:17.455 --> 39:21.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we're using our resources
in the best
way possible without data.

39:22.026 --> 39:29.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Dr. Chris Murray
agrees. That's
why he is crunching the numbers,
in an unprecedented

39:29.667 --> 39:31.502 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
way.

39:31.603 --> 39:32.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. CHRISTOPHER MURRAY, Founder
and Director,
Institute for Health Metrics and
Evaluation:

39:33.037 --> 39:34.172 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We have a 20,000-core
supercomputer, which
is pretty ginormous.

39:34.272 --> 39:36.941 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Big data meets
modern medicine.

39:37.041 --> 39:40.845 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. CHRISTOPHER MURRAY: If you
could identify
all the bits of information out
there, then

39:40.945 --> 39:46.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you would be in the strongest
possible position
to empower people to make better
decisions.

39:46.384 --> 39:52.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Murray is founder
and director
of the Institute for Health
Metrics and Evaluation,

39:52.590 --> 39:58.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a nonprofit that caters to other
nonprofits
seeking to place smart bets.

39:58.129 --> 40:04.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He's the global health
equivalent of legendary
baseball manager Billy Beane,
who first applied

40:04.369 --> 40:09.440 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
big data to the Major Leagues, a
story told
in the 2011 movie "Moneyball."

40:09.540 --> 40:12.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ACTOR: You don't put a team
together with
a computer, Billy.

40:12.977 --> 40:14.279 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BRAD PITT, Actor: No?

40:14.379 --> 40:16.381 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ACTOR: No. Baseball isn't just
numbers.

40:16.481 --> 40:18.583 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BRAD PITT: Adapt or die.

40:18.683 --> 40:22.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. CHRISTOPHER MURRAY: The
difference is
we're not worried about winning
the World

40:22.253 --> 40:25.490 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Series. We're interested in, how
do you make
people healthier?

40:25.590 --> 40:31.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: The data shows
that, globally,
infectious diseases, the red
boxes, are on

40:31.162 --> 40:37.835 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the decline. The U.S. was
declared free of
polio back in 1979. But some
countries continue

40:37.935 --> 40:39.304 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to lag far behind.

40:39.404 --> 40:41.339 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DR. CHRISTOPHER MURRAY: Go to
Niger. Whoa.

40:41.439 --> 40:42.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: Wow.

40:42.907 --> 40:44.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. CHRISTOPHER MURRAY: Let's
see. There you
go. There's where...

40:44.242 --> 40:46.010 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: That's as
dramatic as it gets,
huh?

40:46.110 --> 40:48.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. CHRISTOPHER MURRAY: We know
how to get
rid of infectious diseases,
right, whether

40:48.446 --> 40:51.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
through public health or through
medicine.
And so this is addressable.

40:52.050 --> 40:56.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Quantity is one
thing, but
it's harder to measure a
person's quality

40:56.854 --> 41:04.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of life. So, Murray created a
new metric,
the Disability-Adjusted Life
Year, or DALY.

41:04.495 --> 41:09.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The equation is simple, the
number of years
lost to a premature death, plus
the number

41:09.834 --> 41:16.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of years of good health lost to
a disease
or injury. DALYs make it
possible to measure

41:16.607 --> 41:22.613 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the impact of different
interventions and
show that some hit a lot more
home runs.

41:22.714 --> 41:27.352 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DR. CHRISTOPHER MURRAY:
Individual clinical
care is great for that patient.
You change

41:27.452 --> 41:31.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their lives. But you don't
change the circumstances
of their health, and if you want
to do that,

41:31.956 --> 41:33.725 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you have got to see the bigger
picture.

41:33.825 --> 41:38.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: In the U.S., the
Affordable
Care Act prohibits Medicare from
using tools

41:38.796 --> 41:45.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
like the DALY to ration health
care. Rationing
is considered a dirty word, but
Dr. Singer

41:45.203 --> 41:48.072 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
says the U.S. system is infused
with it.

41:48.172 --> 41:53.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER SINGER: We don't call it
that. We deny
it. But, I mean, I think it's a
crazy system.

41:53.478 --> 41:58.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: He offers the
story of Martin
Shkreli as a case in point. In
September,

41:58.583 --> 42:03.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the pharmaceutical executive
became a poster
boy for greed in U.S. medical
care when he

42:03.688 --> 42:11.829 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
raised the price of an
anti-parasitic drug
from $13.50 to $750 per pill.

42:11.929 --> 42:15.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER SINGER: By denying the
existence of
rationing, we're just writing a
blank check

42:15.700 --> 42:22.073 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to whatever financial
sharpshooter comes in
and sees an opportunity to make
outrageous

42:22.173 --> 42:23.908 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
profits.

42:24.008 --> 42:27.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Outside the U.S.,
there is
less concern about applying big
data to medicine

42:27.512 --> 42:32.750 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the form of DALYs. Mexico was
an early
adopter.

42:32.850 --> 42:36.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Studies showed they should focus
on things
that may not kill, but cause a
great deal

42:36.587 --> 42:42.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of ill health, like depression
and traffic
injuries. And, in Africa, there
has been a

42:42.226 --> 42:45.129 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
dramatic decline in the DALYs
lost to malaria.

42:45.229 --> 42:51.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER SINGER: This has saved
millions of lives,
and that has been largely
data-driven.

42:51.135 --> 42:57.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: But on the front
lines, a statistic
becomes a patient, and things
are less cut

42:57.742 --> 42:59.877 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and dried.

42:59.977 --> 43:05.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Guatemala, Crecencia Buch
(ph) is battling
for her life, threatened by
cervical cancer.

43:05.450 --> 43:12.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CRECENCIA BUCH, Cancer Sufferer
(through translator):
I was told I have cancer, and I
only have

43:12.290 --> 43:14.225 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
seven months to live.

43:14.325 --> 43:21.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: That was back in
2012. An American
NGO, the Maya Health Alliance,
has since spent

43:21.232 --> 43:28.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
almost $10,000 on radiation
therapy, buying
Crecencia few extra years with
her children,

43:28.773 --> 43:32.210 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and now her grandchildren.

43:32.310 --> 43:37.515 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is the sort of heartwarming
image that
has most donors diving for their
wallets.

43:37.615 --> 43:41.018 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But Peter Singer and the
effective altruists
remain unmoved.

43:41.118 --> 43:47.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER SINGER: If you have data
showing that
you will save more lives through
doing something

43:47.458 --> 43:50.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
else, then you should do the
most good you
can.

43:50.561 --> 43:54.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: The DALY bottom
line suggests
the money would have had more
impact if it

43:55.032 --> 44:01.439 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
had been spent on something
else, like Pap
smears to catch cervical cancer
early.

44:01.539 --> 44:08.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But some say DALYs are nothing
more than a
magic bullet approach that is
destined to

44:08.713 --> 44:16.020 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
fail.
DR. Peter Rohloff is founder of
the Maya Health
Alliance. He made the call to
fund Crecencia's

44:16.120 --> 44:17.955 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
treatment.

44:18.055 --> 44:19.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. PETER ROHLOFF, Founder, Maya
Health Alliance:
Giving a mother four years with
her children

44:20.024 --> 44:25.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is precisely a conversation
about living and
not a conversation just about
not dying.

44:26.097 --> 44:30.334 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Dr. Rohloff
believes not everything
can be captured by numbers.

44:30.434 --> 44:33.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. PETER ROHLOFF: We should use
big data,
right? We should be making smart
decisions

44:33.237 --> 44:37.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about how we spend our money.
But the other
half of the global health
equation is the

44:38.042 --> 44:43.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
right to health care. Dreaming
about your
life and where you want your
life to go is

44:43.848 --> 44:49.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a basic human right, and we need
to, I think,
include that in our algorithm,
if such a thing

44:49.520 --> 44:51.355 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
were possible, right?

44:51.455 --> 44:56.928 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Back in Nepal,
Shree Ram Tiwari
works to resuscitate Muna's baby
without power.

44:57.028 --> 45:00.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. SHREE RAM TIWARI (through
translator):
When there is no power, we have
a manually

45:00.898 --> 45:05.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
operated suction device which
